OL,6,FJohn MacKenzie told the High Court in
OL,7,FEdinburgh that he was returning home
OL,8,Ffrom feeding pigs at their croft when
OL,9,Fhe heard someone shouting: "Drop the
OL,10,Fweapon. Drop the weapon."
OL,12,FHe went inside to find his wife Fay
OL,13,Fwith her face covered in blood and a
OL,14,Ftowel around her head. John said they
OL,15,Fwere in the room when his wife, who
OL,16,Fwas looking over his shoulder, said:
OL,17,F"There's the man. There's the man."
